30 class FakeIOPanel(AbstractDigitalIOPanel):

36  def _init_ios(self):
37  self._digital_outputs = OrderedDict([(digital_output["name"], FakeDigitalIO(digital_output["name"],
38  PinMode.DIGITAL_OUTPUT))
39  for digital_output in rospy.get_param("~digital_outputs")])
40 
41  self._digital_inputs = OrderedDict([(digital_input["name"], FakeDigitalIO(digital_input["name"],
42  PinMode.DIGITAL_INPUT))
43  for digital_input in rospy.get_param("~digital_inputs")])
44 
45  for switch in rospy.get_param("~switches"):
46  self._switches_name.append(switch["name"])
47  self._digital_outputs[switch["name"]] = FakeDigitalIO(switch["name"], PinMode.DIGITAL_OUTPUT)
48 
49  def _callback_set_digital_io(self, req):
50  if req.name in self._digital_outputs:
51  self._digital_outputs[req.name].value = req.value
52  elif req.name in self._digital_inputs:
53  self._digital_inputs[req.name].value = req.value
54  elif req.name in self._analog_inputs or req.name in self._analog_outputs:
55  return self._create_response(CommandStatus.DIGITAL_IO_PANEL_ERROR,
56  "{} is not a digital io.".format(req.name))
57  else:
58  # No pin found
59  return self._create_response(CommandStatus.DIGITAL_IO_PANEL_ERROR,
60  "No IO found for {}".format(req.name))
61  self._publish_digital_io_state()
62  return self._create_response(CommandStatus.SUCCESS, "Successfully set value for {}".format(req.name))
